originalText.text: I can't say enough good things about Dr. Anna. She is warm and caring, but will also tell you the good, honest truth. She helped me understand myself more deeply, and gave me many tools to use when I'm struggling. She calls me out when I'm being dishonest to myself, which was invaluable to me. She has also been extremely flexible with my unpredictable schedule and income. She's been in the field for a long time, and continues to educate herself and stay up to date. If you're looking for a superb, intelligent, caring therapist, look no further!

originalText.text: Dr. Anna Fekete is a wonderful therapist. She helped me through a difficult time in my work life and also through many other situations I was looking to speak about. She is strong in how she speaks, intelligent, able to assess situations clearly and quickly, and very easy to talk to. Highly recommend!

originalText.text: I am incredibly grateful for the positive impact Anna has had on my life over the past seven years. She is sincere and flexible, sensitive to changing needs and circumstances. With an impressive background and knowledge base, she maintains a keen awareness of the current zeitgeist, making her relevant and indispensable to people of all backgrounds and identities. I continue to grow in meaningful ways that have improved my relationships and increased my satisfaction with life in general. One can expect a uniquely tailored, sensitive, and professional experience when given the chance to work with Anna.

originalText.text:
I met Dr. Anna before the pandemic; 2019. And little did I know, how much she would enhance my life.

I prefer a therapist that provides feedback along with homework, and she delivers. I know she always has my best interest in mind, and I wholeheartedly trust her advice. She has told me things that may be hard to hear, in the most thoughtful way. This has helped me grow.

She is intuitive, compassionate, empathetic, caring, honest, direct, protective, knowledgeable, all the while being objective.

She has helped me self reflect, challenge the ego, feel empathy for those who have hurt me (not an easy feat), while establishing boundaries. I learned how to mentally challenge myself in order to surpass difficult ordeals. She has built my self confidence, helped me heal my inner child and taught me how to forgive others, for my own health. I have worked on childhood trauma, career changes, health, marriage and family issues.

I honestly don't know how I would have survived the pandemic, along with simultaneous major life changes, without her. I have worked with therapists before her and she has been the most caring, by far. She is truly a lifesaver!

originalText.text: My wife and I began working with Anna during COVID. We were experiencing significant friction after having been married for 13 years. This was the first occasion in our lives when we reached out to work with a therapist. We had worked with another therapist before Anna, and we were still forming our list of requirements for a therapist. We realized that we needed someone who would be very frank with us, even while treating our situation with the care it needed. Anna spent a few sessions understanding our dynamics, personalities, history. And then we started working through the issues. Anna not only advised us and worked through our “issues”, she also shared literature that helped us understand the clinical background to things we were experiencing, and research on the same topics. For us, it was very useful to not just talk about our situation, but also understand that we were not unique. The materials were very revealing. There was no quiz later on. Toward the end of COVID, I decided to explore topics with Anna in personal sessions, and my wife and I were in a significantly better place. I have continued to work with Anna. I find her candor, combined with compassion, very refreshing. Personally, I don’t need someone to tell me that all the ways my issues manifest at my age, are ok. I want to find a way out, and I feel confident that Anna is the right partner for that. I deeply appreciate that her mindset is not for me to be in therapy indefinitely, because I certainly don’t want that. We don’t have a timeline of any kind, but there is certainly a feeling of pushing the ball forward. On basic hygiene factors: Anna is very well read, which comes across (not in an overly academic way, but she always connects her advice/observations to reading and research), always punctual, and prompt with communication. I try not to impose on her personal boundaries with scheduling, but she has always been flexible to accommodate me. Highly recommend working with Anna.
